QtKYq wvgEH pf-36_"><b>Advocating for change</b> - Race Equality Week serves as a rallying cry for policy change and advocacy efforts. Organisations and individuals participating in the initiative join forces to push for systemic reforms that promote racial equity in areas such as education, employment, healthcare, and criminal justice. It's a call to action that can't be ignored.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-38_"><b>Empowering marginalised communities</b> - Raising awareness during Race Equality Week empowers marginalised communities to speak out against racism and discrimination. It provides a platform for their voices to be heard and their concerns to be taken seriously, offering hope and validation to those who have long felt unheard.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-40_"><b>Changing attitudes</b> - Increased awareness can lead to changes in public attitudes and perceptions. Over time, this can result in reduced stereotypes, prejudice, and bias, contributing to a more inclusive and tolerant society.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-42_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/true-support-cropped-shot-of-a-group-of-hands-rea-2023-11-27-04-55-32-utc.jpg?v=1707828610" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/true-support-cropped-shot-of-a-group-of-hands-rea-2023-11-27-04-55-32-utc.jpg?v=1707828610 1536w" width="2000" height="1526" alt="Unlocking workplace equality: A guide to Race Equality Week 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Unlocking workplace equality: A guide to Race Equality Week 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-43_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-44_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="P